SIMPLE: thereabouts
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thereabouts
<hw>There"a*bouts`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[The latter spelling is less
proper, but more commonly used.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Near that
place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Near that number, degree, or quantity; nearly;
<as>as, ten men, or <ex>thereabouts</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Five or six thousand horse . . . or <qex>thereabouts</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some three months since, or <qex>thereabout</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Suckling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Concerning that; about that.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What will ye dine? I will go <qex>thereabout</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were much perplexed <qex>thereabout</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Luke
xxiv. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thereafter</ent>⟦br⟧
